node.text:
Congratulations to @kumasurfboards on winning this years challenge! The board was really fun to ride. Also a huge congrats to the finalists @modernhawaiiancollective @kamaleialexander @acsod @aipasurf @cevichesurfco @axellorentz for making the final! All the boards were so fun. Really appreciate everyone giving it a go and hopefully be back next year bigger and better!! 
Let me know which board you though looked best!!

node.text: Hi all just want to introduce you to @getmentemia a new app that the great @johnkirwan14 created around mental health. This app is here and free to all Australian’s and New Zealanders to help you keep happy and healthy. I have personally had times where I’ve struggled with my own personal Mental Health and I’ve had friends help me out. This app gives you little tips on how to stay grounded, happy and healthy. Give it a look and have fun with it. There’s a link in my bio to get it in the App Store

node.text: The Captains at @starlightau dared me to do something stupid to help put smiles on kids faces in hospital for #starlightday ! I think this will make them laugh haha. @starlightau is an amazing cause and because of these tough times we are going through we can’t go and do hospital visits to cheer up the kids or The Captains can’t go on the streets to raise money. So if you could donate to help kids in hospitals that would be awesome. Or do something stupid like this to celebrate haha link is in my bio. #starlightday thanks for the help @breeanablue

node.text:
We’ll done @owright you kidding an Olympic Bronze medalist. I’ll be honest I shed a tear of Joy to see friends receive Olympic medals. @rissmoore10 and @italoferreira congratulations on becoming the first ever Surfing Gold Medalist🥇 and Bianca Buitendag, @amurotsuzuki and @kanoaigarashi on your medals! 
To all the surfers that competed you should be so proud. You all surfed your hearts out. Was amazing to watch. 
Congrats to my great mates @bededurbo and @kingteeth23 for being coaches on the world stage. Proud of ya lads!

node.text:
Congratulations @julian_wilson on doing you!! Always admired your 100% go for it attitude towards surfing! In the 10 years you were on tour you’ve done what many could never do. Pipe Master, Teahupou (my personal favourite), Portugal, France, Kirra and who could forget J’bay! You pushed the best to be better than their best just to beat you. 

I know this decision is scary and a tremendous amount of thought went into it but there is no wrong decision when you have the support and love of your family. 

Love watching you compete but loved all the good times on tour even more! Proud of you mate! Love ya
